<br>
Having travelled a bit in Asia and Eastern Europe, I can attest that some people have an ability to clearly understand what would sound like utter gibberish to most English-speakers. The converse is also true.  I've met many Americans who were baffled by a London accent, hard as that may be to believe.  It's like they're hearing Greek spoken.<br>
<br>
But back to Everquest. Let me give you to examples.  Myself, I can understand someone perfectly when my language skill is only Good.  For my own sake, it's hardly even worth improving my language skills past Good.  On the other hand, there are people on this board who swear they have trouble understanding someone whose language skill is anything less than Master.  Go figure.<br>
<br>
In other words, it's impossible to answer your question, I'm afraid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 5:36:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> For the case ..</span><hr size=1> .. where only good is available, it's more than OK -- you're doing the best you can.  For the case where both good and master are available, choosing to speak good is intensely annoying.  &quot;Good&quot; is only 61 skill.  It often has every letter garbled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvordul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vordul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 12:32:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For the case ..</span><hr size=1> You sorta become adept at puzzling through the basics of what someone is saying.<br>
